    {
        "content": "<p>tschneidereit <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/3326#issuecomment-916808743\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/3326\">issue #3326</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thank you for the report! The <code>--dir</code> option, as well as many others, is shown when running <code>wasmtime help run</code>. We could consider having an explicit mention of <code>help [subcommand]</code> below the list of subcommands, but I'm not sure how much that'd help.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Another option (which I would be willing to take a shot at if maintainers like the idea) would be<br>\nto use a CLI crate like clap to parse command line arguments and automatically be able to<br>\ngenerate accurate help text from the available options</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>We're using <a href=\"https://docs.rs/structopt/\">structopt</a> for that already. The reason that's slightly less obvious is because all of the interesting bits are inside the various <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/tree/main/src/commands\">commands</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>",
